Package org.eng.aisp.classifier

Defines a general framework for training on and classifying data streams.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IClassifier<DATA>
    Adds trainability to the IFixedClassifier.
    IClassifierBuilder<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Defines function to instantiate new classifiers.
    IClassifierFactory<WINDATA>  
    IFeatureGramClassifier<FDATA>
    Extends the super class to add training on ILabeledFeatureGram instances.
    IFixableClassifier<DATA>
    Defines a trainable classifier from which a IFixedClassifier can be generated.
    IFixableClassifierBuilder<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Overrides the super class to have the IFixableClassifierBuilder.build() method return an IFixableClassifier, a sub-class of IClassifier.
    IFixableUpdatableClassifier<DATA>
    Defines a trainable classifier from which a IFixedClassifier can be generated.
    IFixedClassifier<DATA>
    A implementation that can classify a data sample, but which is not trainable.
    IFixedFeatureGramClassifier<FDATA>
    Abstracts out the classification of IFeatureGrams.
    IUpdatableClassifier<DATA>
    Defines a trainable classifier from which a IFixedClassifier can be generated.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractClassifier<WINDATA>
    Based class for all classifiers.
    AbstractClassifierBuilder<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Supports implementers of IClassifierBuilder.
    AbstractFixableClassifier<WINDATA>
    Extends the superclass to support the implementation of IFixableClassifier.
    AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Provides a base set of function for implementers of IFixableClassifer that need to perform feature extraction.
    AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingUpdatableClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Extends the super class to extract the features from the training data windows.
    AbstractFixableFeatureGramClassifier
    A trainable classifier that uses instances of IFeatureGramClassifier and IFixedFeatureGramClassifier to do the train and classify work.
    AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Extends the super class to implement AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier.classify(IDataWindow).
    Accuracy
    Captures model accuracy information.
    Classification
    Captures the results of a classification produced by an IFixedClassifier.
    Classification.LabelValue  
    Classification.LabelValueComparator
    Used to sort the list of LabelValues into descending (highest first) confidence order.
    ConfusionMatrix
    Generates a Confusion Matrix for two lists of labels.
    FixedFeatureGramClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Extends the super class to implement its methods using an instance of IFixedFeatureGramClassifier.
    FixedSegmentClassifier<WINDATA>
    Provides ability to classify fixed sized subwindows of a given sound.
    KFoldModelEvaluator
    Implements a model evaluation algorithm by holding out 1 of K subsets of training data K times.
    MemoryCachingLabeledFeatureIterable<FDATA>
    Extends the superclass as a convenience to make the generic type system easier to use for ILabeledFeature<>.
    ModelUtil  
    ModelUtil.ClassifierPerformance  
    RESTCallback
    Defines a single URL
    SegmentClassification
    Contains classifications results for a specific segment of an IDataWindow defined by a start and end time in the window.
    TrainingDataPredicate<WINDATA>
    A basic predicate requiring the data windows used for training to 1) optionally have the training label and valid value, and 2) be trainable as defined by its isTrainable() method.
    TrainingSetInfo
    Contains information about a set of ILabeledDataWindows.
    TrainingSetInfo.LabelInfo
    Holds information about all the values that a given label name takes.
    TrainingSetInfo.LabelValueInfo
    Holds information about a single label name/value pair.
    TrainingSoundIterable
    A trivial extension of the super class to allow and encourage users to use the shufflable by-ID iterables.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ConfusionMatrix.Normalization
    Defines the way the percentages are calculated in the Percents confusion matrix via #get

Package org.eng.aisp.classifier Description

Defines a general framework for training on and classifying data streams.
